<chapter xml:id="chapterI-2">
  <title>Sampling</title>

  <objectives permid = "Obj-2">
    <ul permid ="ul-12">
      <li permid ="li-121">
        <p permid ="p-1211">
          Introduce concepts and correct terminology to organize data.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>  
    <p>
      Data must be organized and descripted, this is relevant in any analysis.
    </p>

<p>
How are we going to call a database? To use a common name could leave lack of clarity.
Therefore, people use some characteristics of the database.
  <ul>
    <li>The first word in the first column</li>  
    <li>The number of rows/columns</li>  
  </ul>
This is an informal way to talk about columns, rows, database and more. Then, we proceed to formalize 
some relevant concepts.
  <ul>
    <li><term>Variables</term><idx><h>Variables</h><h>definition of</h></idx> are the formal name to identify columns in a database. 
    This variables represent the <term>Characteristics</term><idx><h>Characteristics</h><h>definition of</h></idx> for each row.</li>
    <li><term>Case</term><idx><h>Case</h><h>definition of</h></idx> is the word to call each row. AKA observational unit.</li>
   <li><term>Data Matrix</term><idx><h>Data</h><h>Matrix</h></idx> is the way to organize data. This is convenient to put in a spreadsheet.</li>
  </ul>
</p>


<example xml:id="exa-I21">
